President Obama released a statement expressing his condolences on the death of First Lieutenant Moaz al-Kasasbeh, who was killed by ISIL terrorists. The President offered his deepest condolences to al-Kasasbeh's family, the Jordan Armed Forces, and the people of Jordan. He praised al-Kasasbeh's bravery and dedication to his country and highlighted his role in the effort to defeat ISIL. The President emphasized the need for unity in the fight against ISIL and the determination to see their ideology eradicated.